        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Currently it is not possible to anonymously bind to a LDAP server - it's required to provide a username and a passwort for a bind. It also is not possible to do an account search without prior binding as a distinct user. But LDAP generally allows for anonymous binds to LDAP servers.\nIt should be no problem to add this feature as the ext\/ldap also provides this functionality.\n\nJust a quick & dirty solution (this surely can be refactored more nicely):\n\nZend\/Ldap.php:\n\nAdd after line 632:\n{code}\nif ($username===null && $password===null) $bindAnonymously=true;\nelse $bindAnonymously=false;\n{code}\n\nChange line 634:\n{code}\nif (!$bindAnonymously && !$username) {\n{code}\n\nChange line 644:\n{code}\nif (!$bindAnonymously && !Zend_Ldap::explodeDn($username)) {\n{code}\n\nChange line 688:\n{code}\n$message = ($bindAnonymously) ? \"anonymous bind\" : $username;\n{code}"
        },
